    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_12",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S represents a pinnacle of the 996 generation, featuring the iconic wide-body silhouette and a robust 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine. Delivering 315 hp through a precise 6-speed manual transaxle, this example boasts an impeccable service history with a documented IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement. The chassis remains taut, utilizing a sophisticated all-wheel-drive system and Porsche Stability Management (PSM) for surgical cornering. Finished in a flawless Arctic Silver Metallic over Supple Leather, the exterior shows no signs of rock chips or clear coat failure, while the undercarriage remains dry and free of oxidation. Mechanical highlights include factory-optioned sport exhaust, cross-drilled rotors with four-piston monoblock calipers, and a perfectly calibrated suspension that retains its original damping characteristics. This is a collector-grade specimen for the discerning purist.",
